I am very disappointed by this. I had a lot of fun with the previous installment, not so much here. The problem is that 95% of the insults makes no sense whatsoever. Most of the insults you can formulate will be like this one: "A damsel in distress just doesn't get your mentor and was rebooted by JJ Abrams" The characters you can choose are uninteresting. One would think that with Hollywood as your theme, the creators of the game would have an infinite amount of funny/interesting people to draw inspiration from... And what could've been interesting just isn't. Like the Deadpool character. Doesn't sound like Deadpool or anything, just looks like him. The presentation is great though.

Love the game - it's almost identical to its predecessor, so if you liked that, you'll like this also. My only gripe is that, despite claiming controller support, the Nvidia Shield controller is *not* supported. You'd think the controller that goes with the number one gaming tablet (also the number one Android device used to connect and play on TV, which benefits from controller support greatly) would be one of the first controllers they'd add, but so far it has no input capabilities whatsoever. If this is fixed, I'll up my rating to five stars. It really is a good game. Just needs Shield controller support.
